---
id: org.dxos.plugin.tictactoe
name: TicTacToePlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A configurable Tic-Tac-Toe game plugin for DXOS Composer with multiplayer and AI opponents.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Types

```mdl
type Marker
  literals: X | O
```

```mdl
type Difficulty
  literals: easy | medium | hard
```

```mdl
type GameStatus
  literals: playing | x-wins | o-wins | draw
```

```mdl
type Player
  fields:
    id?: string               # DID of the player
    marker: Marker
```

```mdl
type Game
  fields:
    name?: string
    board: string             # flat string of length size*size; '-' = empty, 'X' or 'O' = placed
    moves?: string            # semicolon-separated move log, e.g. "X:1,1;O:0,2;X:2,0"
    size: number              # board dimension (3, 4, or 5)
    winCondition: number      # consecutive marks needed to win
    difficulty?: Difficulty   # AI difficulty when playing against AI
    status: GameStatus
    players:
      x?: string              # DID of X player
      o?: string              # DID of O player
```

## Components

```mdl
component TicTacToeBoard
  desc: Pure N×N grid rendered with CSS Grid. Shows X/O markers as colored SVG shapes with placement animations.
  props:
    board: string
    size: number
    winningCells?: number[]   # indices of cells in the winning line
    disabled: boolean
  state:
    hovered?: number          # cell index under cursor
  actions:
    onCellClick(row: number, col: number)
  layout: |
    ┌───┬───┬───┐
    │ X │   │ O │
    ├───┼───┼───┤
    │   │ X │   │
    ├───┼───┼───┤
    │ O │   │ X │
    └───┴───┴───┘
```

```mdl
component GameStatus
  desc: Displays current turn, winner, or draw state with player identity.
  props:
    status: GameStatus
    currentTurn: Marker
    playerX?: string
    playerO?: string
```

```mdl
component TicTacToeArticle
  desc: Main game surface. Connects ECHO game object to board, handles move logic, AI turns, and settings.
  props:
    subject: Game
    role: string
    attendableId?: string
  state:
    aiThinking: boolean
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  actions:
    makeMove(row: number, col: number)
    newGame()
    updateSettings(size: number, winCondition: number, difficulty: Difficulty)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar: settings]     │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ GameStatus              │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │                         │
    │    TicTacToeBoard       │
    │                         │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component TicTacToeCard
  desc: Compact card view showing mini board and game status.
  props:
    subject: Game
    role: string
  layout: |
    ┌──────────┐
    │ mini grid│
    │  status  │
    └──────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service TicTacToeAI
  desc: Local AI engine with configurable difficulty.
  ops:
    computeMove(board: string, size: number, winCondition: number, marker: Marker, difficulty: Difficulty) → number
  errors:
    NoMovesAvailable: board is full or game is over
```

```mdl
service GameStore
  desc: Persists and replicates Game state via ECHO.
  ops:
    create(name?: string, size: number, winCondition: number, difficulty?: Difficulty) → Game
    load(id: string) → Game
    save(game: Game) → Game
  effects: [echo:write, echo:read]
```

## Operations

Pure operations:

```mdl
op checkWin
  desc: Checks if the board has a winner or is a draw.
  input:
    board: string
    size: number
    winCondition: number
  output: GameStatus
```

```mdl
op getValidMoves
  desc: Returns indices of empty cells.
  input:
    board: string
  output: number[]
```

Effectful operations:

```mdl
op create
  desc: Creates a new Tic-Tac-Toe game.
  input:
    name?: string
    size?: number             # default 3
    winCondition?: number     # default equals size
    difficulty?: Difficulty   # default medium
  output: Game
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [GameStore]
```

```mdl
op makeMove
  desc: Places a marker on the board and updates game state.
  input:
    game: Game
    position: string          # "row,col" e.g. "1,2"
  output:
    board: string
    status: GameStatus
  errors:
    CellOccupied: target cell is not empty
    GameOver: game has already ended
    WrongTurn: not the player's turn
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [GameStore]
```

```mdl
op aiMove
  desc: Uses the AI engine to play the next move.
  input:
    game: Game
    difficulty?: Difficulty   # overrides game default
  output:
    board: string
    status: GameStatus
    position: string          # the position the AI chose
  errors:
    GameOver: game has already ended
  requires: [TicTacToeAI, GameStore]
```

```mdl
op print
  desc: Prints the board to ASCII for assistant context.
  input:
    board: string
    size: number
  output:
    ascii: string
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Create Game

  req F-1.1: New game created with empty board of configured size.
  req F-1.2: X always moves first.
  req F-1.3: Win condition defaults to board size but can be overridden.
  req F-1.4: Game persisted to ECHO and visible in space.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Make Move

  req F-2.1:
    when: player clicks an empty cell on their turn
    then: marker placed, board string updated, turn advances

  req F-2.2:
    when: player clicks an occupied cell
    then: move rejected, no state change

  req F-2.3:
    when: move completes a winning line
    then: status set to x-wins or o-wins, winning cells highlighted with animation

  req F-2.4:
    when: board is full with no winner
    then: status set to draw
```

```mdl
feat F-3: AI Opponent

  req F-3.1:
    when: game has AI enabled and it is AI's turn
    then: AI computes and plays a move after a brief delay

  req F-3.2: Easy difficulty plays random valid moves.
  req F-3.3: Medium difficulty uses heuristic (block wins, take wins, prefer center).
  req F-3.4: Hard difficulty uses minimax with alpha-beta pruning.
  req F-3.5: AI thinking state shown in UI during computation.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Multiplayer

  req F-4.1: Two players in the same ECHO space can join as X and O.
  req F-4.2: Board state synced via ECHO in real-time.
  req F-4.3: Moves from remote player appear with placement animation.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Configurable Board

  req F-5.1: Board size selectable as 3×3, 4×4, or 5×5.
  req F-5.2: Win condition adjustable (e.g., 4-in-a-row on a 5×5 board).
  req F-5.3: Settings changeable at game creation or via new game action.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Blueprint Integration

  req F-6.1: Assistant can create games, make moves, and analyze board state.
  req F-6.2: Assistant can play as an opponent using AI operations.
  req F-6.3: Print operation provides ASCII board for assistant context.
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Visual Polish

  req F-7.1: X and O rendered as colored SVG shapes (distinct hues).
  req F-7.2: Scale-in animation on marker placement.
  req F-7.3: Winning cells pulse/glow on game end.
  req F-7.4: Board uses TailwindCSS, fits DXOS design system.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: New game default state
  given: a new 3×3 game is created
  then:
    - board is 9 characters, all '-'
    - status === playing
    - size === 3
    - winCondition === 3
```

```mdl
test T-2: Valid move updates board
  given: new 3×3 game, X's turn
  when: X plays at position 1,1
  then:
    - board[4] === 'X' (center cell)
    - moves contains "X:1,1"
    - current turn is O
```

```mdl
test T-3: Occupied cell rejected
  given: game with X at position 0,0
  when: O attempts to play at 0,0
  then: CellOccupied error, board unchanged
```

```mdl
test T-4: Win detection
  given: 3×3 game, X at 0,0 and 0,1
  when: X plays at 0,2
  then:
    - status === x-wins
    - winningCells === [0, 1, 2]
```

```mdl
test T-5: Draw detection
  given: 3×3 game with 8 cells filled, no winner
  when: last cell is played
  then: status === draw
```

```mdl
test T-6: AI plays after human move
  given: game with AI enabled (medium), human is X
  when: X makes a move
  then:
    - AI thinking indicator shown
    - AI places O on a valid cell
    - turn returns to X
```

```mdl
test T-7: Multiplayer sync
  given: two players in shared ECHO space, active game
  when: player X makes a move
  then: player O's board updates with X's marker and animation
  tags: [collaborative]
```

```mdl
test T-8: Configurable board size
  given: a new 5×5 game with winCondition 4
  when: game is created
  then:
    - board is 25 characters, all '-'
    - size === 5
    - winCondition === 4
```

```mdl
test T-9: Hard AI plays optimally
  given: 3×3 game, hard AI is O, X has played center
  when: AI makes a move
  then: AI plays a corner (optimal response to center opening)
```

```mdl
test T-10: Blueprint create and move
  given: assistant uses create operation
  when: assistant calls makeMove with position "0,0"
  then:
    - board updated with marker
    - assistant receives updated board and status
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
